PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)

App Name: MimiPro – Distributor Delivery & Business Manager

1. PURPOSE & VISION

1.1 Purpose

MimiPro is an offline-first Android business management app designed for distributors in Bangladesh to manage:

Daily delivery calculations

Product stock movement

Employee attendance & salary

Deliveryman & helper assignment

Business credit tracking

Monthly history & reporting

The app runs as an HTML/JS app inside Android WebView, storing data locally (IndexedDB) with future cloud sync support.

1.2 Target Users

Small & medium distributors

Owners who manage deliverymen and helpers

Businesses operating without permanent internet

2. TECH STACK (CURRENT & FUTURE)

2.1 Current Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript

Storage: IndexedDB (local)

Android: WebView (Java + XML wrapper)

Offline-first by default

2.2 Future (Optional)

Firebase Realtime Database (sync only)

Manual or automatic backup

Multi-device access for owner only

3. CORE ENTITIES & DATA MODELS

3.1 Product

Copy code

Product {

  id

  name

  unitPrice

}

3.2 Delivery Record

Copy code

Delivery {

  id

  date

  deliverymanId

  helperIds[]

  items[] {

    productId

    sentQty

    returnedQty

    soldQty (auto calculated)

    price

    total

  }

  grandTotal

}

Calculation Logic

Copy code

soldQty = sentQty - returnedQty

itemTotal = soldQty × price

grandTotal = sum(itemTotal)

3.3 Employee (Deliveryman / Helper)

Copy code

Employee {

  id

  name

  role (deliveryman | helper)

  phone

  passwordHash

  salaryType (daily | monthly)

  salaryRate

  isActive

}

3.4 Attendance

Copy code

Attendance {

  employeeId

  date

  status (present | absent)

}

3.5 Salary Advance

Copy code

SalaryAdvance {

  employeeId

  date

  amount

  note

}

3.6 Business Credit

Copy code

BusinessCredit {

  id

  name

  date

  totalAmount

  paidAmount

  remainingAmount

}

4. AUTHENTICATION MODEL (EMPLOYEE SECURITY)

Selected Option: B – Employee ID + Password

Rules:

Each employee has:

Unique Employee ID

Password

Employees can:

Log in only to their own ID

View only their attendance & salary

Owner/Admin:

No login restriction

Can access all data

Security Logic

Password stored as hashed value

No employee can view another employee’s data

Owner bypasses login

5. PAGE-BY-PAGE REQUIREMENTS

PAGE 1: HOME / DASHBOARD

UI Components

Header (App name)

Grid / Cards:

Delivery

Attendance

Employees

Business Credit

Products

History

Functional Logic

Entry point for all modules

Shows today’s date

PAGE 2: DELIVERY CALCULATION PAGE

UI

Date selector (default today)

Deliveryman selector (dropdown)

Helper selector (multi-select)

Product list table:

Product name

Sent

Returned

Sold (auto)

Price

Total (auto)

Grand total display

Save button

Logic

Sold auto-calculated

Cannot save without selecting deliveryman

Data stored locally

PAGE 3: EMPLOYEE MANAGEMENT

UI

Employee list

Add button (bottom-right)

Employee detail view

Add Employee Fields

Name

Role (deliveryman/helper)

Phone

Salary type

Salary rate

Password

PAGE 4: ATTENDANCE PAGE

UI

Date selector

Employee list with Present/Absent toggle

Save attendance

Logic

One attendance record per employee per day

Used later in salary calculation

PAGE 5: SALARY & ADVANCE PAGE

UI

Month selector

Employee selector

Attendance summary

Salary calculation

Advance deduction list

Final payable amount

Salary Logic

Daily Salary

Copy code

salary = presentDays × dailyRate

Monthly Salary

Copy code

salary = monthlyRate (if any presence)

Final Pay

Copy code

finalPay = salary - sum(advances)

PAGE 6: BUSINESS CREDIT PAGE

UI

Month selector

Credit list (box style)

Each credit shows:

Name

Date

Total

Paid

Remaining

Add Credit button

Add Payment option per credit

Logic

Copy code

remaining = totalAmount - paidAmount

PAGE 7: PRODUCT MANAGEMENT

UI

Product list

Add/Edit/Delete

Price update support

PAGE 8: HISTORY PAGE (MONTHLY)

UI

Single page scroll

Sections per month:

Delivery list

Monthly total sales

Credit summary

Logic

Data grouped by month

No filtering required by default

6. DATA STORAGE & PERSISTENCE

Storage Rules

All data saved in IndexedDB

No data loss on reload

Each module has its own store

Backup (Future)

Manual export

Firebase sync (owner only)

7. UI / UX GUIDELINES

Clean, flat UI

Large touch targets

No clutter

Offline friendly

Bangla-friendly text support

8. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

Works without internet

Fast load (<1s)

No crashes on navigation

Handles years of data

9. FUTURE EXTENSIONS (NOT REQUIRED NOW)

